lass=\"moduletable-sfx4\">\r\n<p>Reactome provides <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source\">open-source</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_data\">open-data</a>. We have continuously supported the major open-data standards, including <a href=\"http://www.biopax.org/\">BioPAX</a>, <a href=\"http://www.psidev.info/groups/molecular-interactions\">PSI-MITAB</a>, <a href=\"http://sbml.org/\">SBML</a> and <a href=\"http://www.sbgn.org/\">SBGN</a> export formats. The Reactome data and source code continues to be publicly accessible under the terms of a Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported License.</p>\r\n<h3>Graph Database</h3>\r\n<p>For more information on the installation of the Reactome Graph Database, please refer to the&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=45#GetStarted\">Get Started</a>&nbsp;section of the&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=45\">Graph Database</a>&nbsp;documentation in the&nbsp;<a href=\"dev\">Developer Guide</a>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/reactome.graphdb.tgz\">Reactome Graph Database</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Services and GitHub Repository</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>Content Service</strong>: Our new <a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=48#Resources\">Content Service</a> provides outside users with direct access to pathway data in Reactome.</li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><strong>Analysis Service</strong>: The Reactome Pathway <a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=47#Resources\" style=\"text-align: justify; font-size: 14px;\">Analysis Tools</a><span style=\"text-align: justify; color: #333333; font-size: 14px;\"> are also available for integration into third party websites.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: circle;\"><a href=\"https://github.com/reactome\">GitHub Repository Repository</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Identifier mapping files</h3>\r\n<p>Mapping files link the source database identifier to the lowest level pathway diagram or subset of the pathway, all levels of the pathway hierarchy or database identifier to all reactions. {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=60\"}Read more{/modal}&nbsp;about the format.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Lowest level pathway diagram / Subset of the pathway\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2Reactome.txt\">UniProt to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2Reactome.txt\">ChEBI to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome.txt\">ENSEMBL to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2Reactome.txt\">miRBase to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2Reactome.txt\">NCBI to pathways</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>All levels of the pathway hierarchy\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2Reactome_All_Levels.txt\">UniProt to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2Reactome_All_Levels.txt\">ChEBI to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome_All_Levels.txt\">ENSEMBL to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2Reactome_All_Levels.txt\">miRBase to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2Reactome_All_Levels.txt\">NCBI to All pathways</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Database identifier to all reactions\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2ReactomeReactions.txt\">UniProt to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2ReactomeReactions.txt\">ChEBI to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2ReactomeReactions.txt\">ENSEMBL to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2ReactomeReactions.txt\">miRBase to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2ReactomeReactions.txt\">NCBI to All reactions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Physical Entity (PE) Identifier mapping files</h3>\r\n<p>Mapping files link the source database identifier to the lowest level pathway diagram or subset of the pathway. {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=86\"}Read more{/modal}&nbsp;about the format.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Lowest level pathway diagram / Subset of the pathway\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2Reactome_PE_Pathway.txt\">UniProt to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2Reactome_PE_Pathway.txt\">ChEBI to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome_PE_Pathway.txt\">ENSEMBL to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2Reactome_PE_Pathway.txt\">miRBase to pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2Reactome_PE_Pathway.txt\">NCBI to pathways</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>All levels of the pathway hierarchy\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2Reactome_PE_All_Levels.txt\">UniProt to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2Reactome_PE_All_Levels.txt\">ChEBI to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome_PE_All_Levels.txt\">ENSEMBL to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2Reactome_PE_All_Levels.txt\">miRBase to All pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2Reactome_PE_All_Levels.txt\">NCBI to All pathways</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Database identifier to all reactions\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/UniProt2Reactome_PE_Reactions.txt\">UniProt to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ChEBI2Reactome_PE_Reactions.txt\">ChEBI to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ensembl2Reactome_PE_Reactions.txt\">ENSEMBL to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/miRBase2Reactome_PE_Reactions.txt\">miRBase to All reactions</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/NCBI2Reactome_PE_Reactions.txt\">NCBI to All reactions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Other Mappings</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/models2pathways.tsv\">BioModels to Pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ReactionPMIDS.txt\">Reaction PMIDs</a> - {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=87\"}Read more{/modal} about the format</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Reactome2OMIM.txt\">Reactome to OMIM</a> - {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=88\"}Read more{/modal} about the format</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ProteinRoleReaction.txt\">Protein Role Reaction</a> - {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=89\"}Read more{/modal} about the format</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Pathways</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Pathway Information. {modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=61\"}Read more{/modal} about the format\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ReactomePathways.txt\">Complete List of Pathways</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ReactomePathwaysRelation.txt\">Pathways hierarchy relationship</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Complex_2_Pathway_human.txt\">Complexes to Pathways (Human)</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/Ewas2Pathway_human.txt\">EWAS to Pathways (Human)</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>Pathway Diagrams and Illustrations\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i>Human pathway diagrams: <a href=\"/download/current/diagrams.pdf.zip\">PDF</a> or <a href=\"/download/current/diagrams.png.zip\">PNG</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i>Human Pathway Illustrations: <a href=\"/download/current/ehlds.tgz\">SVG</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Reactome External Identifiers</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/reactome_stable_ids.txt\">Reactome Stable Identifiers</a>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Protein-Protein Interactions derived from Reactome pathways</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>{modal url=\"https://psicquic.github.io/MITAB27Format.html\"}PSI-MITAB format{/modal} interaction files\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/interactors/reactome.all_species.interactions.psi-mitab.txt\">All interactions, including non-human species</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/interactors/reactome.homo_sapiens.interactions.psi-mitab.txt\" title=\"Human protein-protein interactions\">Human protein-protein interactions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-folder\"></i>{modal url=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=62\"}TAB-delimited format{/modal} formatted files\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/interactors/reactome.all_species.interactions.tab-delimited.txt\">All interactions, including non-human species</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/interactors/reactome.homo_sapiens.interactions.tab-delimited.txt\">Human protein-protein interactions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"display: none;\">Deprecated interaction files:\r\n<ul style=\"display: none;\">\r\n<li><a href=\"/download/current/interactors/reactome.homo_sapiens.interactions.tab-delimited.txt\">Human protein-protein interactions</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.reactome.org/download/interactions.README.txt\">tab-delimited format</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/download/interactions.README.txt\"></a><a href=\"http://www.reactome.org/download/all_interactions.html\">Full list of protein-protein interactions, including non-human species</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"display: none;\"><a href=\"http://www.reactome.org/download/all_interactions.html\" style=\"list-style-type: none;\"></a><span class=\"info-box warning-box\">Please note that these protein-protein interaction files will no longer available after Version 62.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Specialized data formats</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/gene_association.reactome\">Gene association file (GO annotation in Reactome)</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/homo_sapiens.3.1.sbml.tgz\">Human reactions</a> in SBML&nbsp;&nbsp;(level 3, version 1) format (new)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/all_species.3.1.sbml.tgz\">All Species reactions</a>&nbsp;in SBML&nbsp;&nbsp;(level 3, version 1) format (new)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i>Events in the <a href=\"/download/current/biopax2.zip\">BioPAX level 2 </a>format.</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i>Events in the <a href=\"/download/current/biopax.zip\">BioPAX level 3 </a>format.</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i>Events in the <a href=\"/download/current/homo_sapiens.sbgn.tar.gz\">SBGN</a> format.</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/ReactomePathways.gmt.zip\">Reactome Pathways Gene Set</a>.</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\"></i>Protégé 2.0 ontology for Reactome data model: <a href=\"/download/current/reactome_data_model.pins\">pins file</a>, <a href=\"/download/current/reactome_data_model.pont\">pont file</a>, <a href=\"/download/current/reactome_data_model.pprj\">pprj file</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Functional interactions (FIs) derived from Reactome, and other pathway and interaction databases</h3>\r\n<p>For details about FIs, please see&nbsp;<a href=\"http://genomebiology.com/content/11/5/R53\">Wu G, Feng X, Stein L</a>. To use these FI networks, please try our&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=44\" title=\"ReactomeFIViz Cytoscape app\">ReactomeFIViz Cytoscape app</a>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"http://reactomews.oicr.on.ca:8080/caBigR3WebApp2016/FIsInGene_022717_with_annotations.txt.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Version 2016</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"http://reactomews.oicr.on.ca:8080/caBigR3WebApp2015/FIsInGene_031516_with_annotations.txt.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Version 2015</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"http://reactomews.oicr.on.ca:8080/caBigR3WebApp2014/FIsInGene_121514_with_annotations.txt.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Version 2014</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"http://reactomews.oicr.on.ca:8080/caBigR3WebApp2013/FIsInGene_121013_with_annotations.txt.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Version 2013</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>MySQL dumps of Reactome databases</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/databases/gk_current.sql.gz\">Main database</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/databases/gk_current_dn.sql.gz\">Simplified database</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/databases/gk_stable_ids.sql.gz\">Stable identifiers database</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Curation Software</h3>\r\n<p>The Curator tool is meant for use by curators to annotate biological pathways based on the Reactome schema. Please note that this tool will only work with a database using our internal database format; the database available from this web page will not work with them.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-book\"></i><a href=\"index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=63\">Curator Tool (version 3.1, build 89, November 30, 2017)</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Reactome textbook of biological pathways and processes</h3>\r\n<p>Note: RTF files may be very large, but conversion to PDF or Word generates a file that is much smaller with no loss of information</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/TheReactomeBook.pdf.zip\">PDF</a></li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fa fa-file-zip-o\"></i><a href=\"/download/current/TheReactomeBook.rtf.zip\">RTF format</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','',1,32,'2017-01-01 09:00:00',156,'','2017-01-01 09:00:00',156,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2017-04-21 14:47:36','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_capt